<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"mso-line-height-alt:.75pt"><span style=3D"fo=
nt-size:1.0pt;color:white">Hi Grant, Yes =E2=80=93 David=E2=80=99s team can c=
ommence cleaning of the mid-floor level tomorrow, strictly on the basis that=
 this work is limited to what is necessary to allow
 full assessment of the damage and to determine the scope and cost of repair=
 works,<o:p></o:p></span></p>
</div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"mso-line-height-alt:.75pt"><span style=3D"fo=
nt-size:1.0pt;color:white"><o:p></o:p></span></p>
</div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal">Hi Grant,<o:p></o:p></p>
</div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>
</div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal">Yes =E2=80=93 David=E2=80=99s team can commence clean=
ing of the mid-floor level tomorrow, strictly on the basis that this work is=
 limited to what is necessary to allow full assessment of the damage and to d=
etermine the scope and cost of repair works, and
 will not remove, cover, or alter any areas that still require inspection fo=
r damage, safety, or compliance purposes.
<span style=3D"color:#0070C0">Acknowledged and agreed =E2=80=93 Davids team w=
ill complete cleaning only. Point of clarification =E2=80=93 I need them to r=
emove target areas of wall linings so we can continue to determine the resul=
ting damage. So in doing this =E2=80=93 they are enabling
 us to continue with correct and ongoing assessment, as we cannot inspect th=
e wall cavity in targeted areas with wall linings in place. &nbsp;</span><o:=
p></o:p></p>
</div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>
</div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal">In particular, can we please also arrange to assess t=
he roof and the gas unit as part of this stage, so that any issues are ident=
ified before assessing the damage and determining the scope and cost of repa=
ir works?
<span style=3D"color:#0070C0">Agreed and acknowledged. We did access the roo=
f space during our visit yesterday and I will enlist the services of the ser=
vice contractor to make a formal assessment of the gas exchange unit. They a=
re the specialist provider on this
 unit =E2=80=93 so I will seek their professional advice on the next steps r=
equired to include this unit in the assessment. &nbsp;&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></spa=
n></p>
</div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>
</div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal">Regarding contents, there is still a substantial amou=
nt to go through both upstairs and downstairs. Could you please confirm what=
 the plan and timeline are for completing the contents assessment?
<span style=3D"color:#0070C0">I understand that the downstairs will be compl=
ete by now. I will have David comment further on this subject.<o:p></o:p></s=
pan></p>
</div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>
</div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal">Lastly, I would like to engage a structural engineer f=
or damage assessment. As requested in my 1 July email, please confirm whethe=
r Tower requires prior approval for this, and provide the relevant policy gu=
idelines or procedures for reimbursement
 of claims preparation work. <o:p></o:p></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-family:&quot;Aptos Display&quot;,=
sans-serif;color:#0070C0">Tower Insurance will not need to engage a CPEng to=
 determine repair details.
</span><span style=3D"font-family:&quot;Aptos Display&quot;,sans-serif;color=
:#0070C0">Stephen walker will complete the structural detailing required to d=
etermine the framing repairs to the dwelling as this is within the scope lim=
itations of the
</span><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-family:&quot;Aptos Display&quot;,s=
ans-serif;color:#0070C0;mso-fareast-language:EN-US">Standard NZS 3604:2011.<=
o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-family:&quot;Aptos=
 Display&quot;,sans-serif;color:#0070C0;mso-fareast-language:EN-US">The enga=
gement of ASURNZ to provide this report and the details required to complete=
 the repairs is at Towers own cost.</span><span style=3D"font-family:&quot;A=
ptos Display&quot;,sans-serif;color:#0070C0"><o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-family:&quot;Aptos Display&quot;,=
sans-serif;color:#0070C0">Stephen Walker has provided the following statemen=
t and has also provided the attached qualifications and capability statement=
s for your reference:<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:10.0pt;font-f=
amily:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;color:#275317;mso-style-textfill-fill-col=
or:#275317;mso-style-textfill-fill-alpha:100.0%;mso-fareast-language:EN-US">=
<o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:10.0pt;font-f=
amily:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;color:#275317;mso-style-textfill-fill-col=
or:#275317;mso-style-textfill-fill-alpha:100.0%;mso-fareast-language:EN-US">=
Hi Grant,<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:10.0pt;font-f=
amily:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;color:#275317;mso-style-textfill-fill-col=
or:#275317;mso-style-textfill-fill-alpha:100.0%;mso-fareast-language:EN-US">=
<o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:10.0pt;font-f=
amily:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;color:#275317;mso-style-textfill-fill-col=
or:#275317;mso-style-textfill-fill-alpha:100.0%;mso-fareast-language:EN-US">=
Please see attached as requested.&nbsp; I have also
 included copy of our legislative and regulatory capability statement.<o:p><=
/o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:10.0pt;font-f=
amily:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;color:#275317;mso-style-textfill-fill-col=
or:#275317;mso-style-textfill-fill-alpha:100.0%;mso-fareast-language:EN-US">=
<o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:10.0pt;font-f=
amily:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;color:#275317;mso-style-textfill-fill-col=
or:#275317;mso-style-textfill-fill-alpha:100.0%;mso-fareast-language:EN-US">=
Note that this building is within the scope limitations
 of the Standard NZS 3604:2011.&nbsp; NZS 3604:2011 is a cited means of comp=
liance with building code clause B1 =E2=80=93 Structure for timber framed bu=
ildings not requiring specific engineering design.&nbsp; This means that the=
re is no legislative requirement for engaging a
 structural engineer for design requirements for the repair of this building=
.&nbsp; As such, any repair or construction carried out in accordance with t=
he Standard is deemed to satisfy the relevant provisions of the building cod=
e and the Building Act 2004.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:10.0pt;font-f=
amily:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;color:#275317;mso-style-textfill-fill-col=
or:#275317;mso-style-textfill-fill-alpha:100.0%;mso-fareast-language:EN-US">=
<o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:10.0pt;font-f=
amily:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;color:#275317;mso-style-textfill-fill-col=
or:#275317;mso-style-textfill-fill-alpha:100.0%;mso-fareast-language:EN-US">=
Further, considering the knowledge and experience
 provided by ASURNZ personnel regarding the assessment of fire damaged timbe=
r framed buildings, including my knowledge and experience, I doubt there wou=
ld be any additional benefit gained by engaging a structural engineer for th=
is claim.&nbsp; However, should any
 design requirements that sit outside the scope limitations of NZS 3604:2011=
 and that require specific engineering design become apparent during scoping=
 of repairs, I confirm that we will in that instance seek engineering design=
 from a suitably experienced
 Chartered Professional Engineer (CPEng).<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:10.0pt;font-f=
amily:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;color:#275317;mso-style-textfill-fill-col=
or:#275317;mso-style-textfill-fill-alpha:100.0%;mso-fareast-language:EN-US">=
